Note: ========================================
Note: HIR to SQL Generator
Note: ========================================
Note: Generates PostgreSQL SQL from Runa HIR dictionary representation
Note:
Note: Part of the Translation translation system - SQL backend
Note:
Note: This generator takes HIR dictionaries (as created by sql_to_hir.runa)
Note: and produces valid PostgreSQL SQL statements.
Note:
Note: Architecture:
Note:   - Context-based generation with SQL emitter
Note:   - Dictionary dispatch based on "type" field
Note:   - Complete SELECT statement generation
Note:   - Complete INSERT statement generation
Note:   - Expression generation (binary ops, literals, function calls)
Note:   - Proper SQL formatting with keywords and identifiers
Note: ========================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/sql/sql_emitter.runa" as Emitter
Import "stdlib/core/string.runa" as StringCore
Import "stdlib/core/list.runa" as List
Import "stdlib/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ========================================
Note: SQL Generator Context
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generator context manages the SQL emitter and generation state.
This provides consistent state management during SQL generation.
@End Reasoning

Type called "SQLGeneratorContext":
    emitter as Integer          Note: SQL emitter instance
    indent_level as Integer     Note: Current indentation level (for pretty printing)
End Type

Process called "create_generator_context" returns Integer:
    Note: Create new SQL generator context

    Let context be proc allocate from Layout with 16

    Let emitter be proc create_sql_emitter from Emitter
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 0, emitter

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with context, 8, 0  Note: indent_level = 0

    Return context
End Process

Process called "destroy_generator_context" takes context as Integer:
    Note: Destroy generator context and free resources

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    proc destroy_sql_emitter from Emitter with emitter

    proc deallocate from Layout with context
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Main Entry Point
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Main entry point for HIR→SQL generation. Takes HIR dictionary
and returns generated SQL as a string pointer.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_sql_from_hir" takes hir_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate SQL from HIR dictionary representation
    Note: Returns: Pointer to generated SQL string (caller must deallocate)

    Let context be proc create_generator_context

    proc generate_hir_node with context, hir_node

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    Let sql_output be proc get_output from Emitter with emitter

    proc destroy_generator_context from context

    Return sql_output
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: HIR Node Generation (Dictionary Dispatch)
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Dispatch HIR dictionary to appropriate generator based on "type" field.
This provides a clean separation of concerns for different SQL constructs.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_hir_node" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate SQL for any HIR node (dictionary dispatch)

    Let node_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir_node

    Note: Check for dictionary type (all SQL structures are dictionaries)
    If node_type is not equal to 7:  Note: HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL = 7
        Note: Not a dictionary, might be literal - generate literal
        proc generate_literal with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If

    Note: Get "type" field from dictionary
    Let type_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "type"
    Let type_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, type_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with type_key

    If type_value is equal to 0:
        Note: No "type" field, might be a literal dictionary
        proc generate_literal with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If

    Note: Extract type string value
    Let type_str be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with type_value
    Let type_len be proc string_length from StringCore with type_str

    Note: Dispatch based on type string
    Let select_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "select"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, select_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with select_type
        proc generate_select_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with select_type

    Let insert_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "insert"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, insert_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with insert_type
        proc generate_insert_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with insert_type

    Let binary_op_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "binary_op"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, binary_op_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with binary_op_type
        proc generate_binary_operation with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with binary_op_type

    Let function_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "function"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, function_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with function_type
        proc generate_function_call with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with function_type

    Let column_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "column"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, column_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with column_type
        proc generate_column_reference with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with column_type

    Let join_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "join"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, join_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with join_type
        proc generate_join_clause with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with join_type

    Let update_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "update"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, update_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with update_type
        proc generate_update_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with update_type

    Let delete_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "delete"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, delete_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with delete_type
        proc generate_delete_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with delete_type

    Let create_table_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "create_table"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, create_table_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with create_table_type
        proc generate_create_table_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with create_table_type

    Let alter_table_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "alter_table"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, alter_table_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with alter_table_type
        proc generate_alter_table_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with alter_table_type

    Let drop_type be proc create_string from StringCore with "drop"
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with type_str, drop_type is equal to 1:
        proc deallocate from Layout with drop_type
        proc generate_drop_statement with context, hir_node
        Return
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with drop_type

    Note: Unknown type, treat as literal
    proc generate_literal with context, hir_node
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: SELECT Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generate complete SELECT statements with all clauses:
SELECT [DISTINCT] columns FROM table [JOIN...] [WHERE...]
[GROUP BY...] [HAVING...] [ORDER BY...] [LIMIT...] [OFFSET...]
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_select_statement" takes context as Integer, select_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate SELECT statement from HIR dictionary

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: SELECT keyword
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "SELECT"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Check for DISTINCT
    Let distinct_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "distinct"
    Let distinct_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, distinct_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with distinct_key

    If distinct_value is not equal to 0:
        Let is_distinct be proc get_hir_boolean_value from HIR with distinct_value

        If is_distinct is equal to 1:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "DISTINCT"
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If
    End If

    Note: Generate SELECT list (columns)
    Let columns_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "columns"
    Let columns_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, columns_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with columns_key

    If columns_list is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_column_list with context, columns_list
    Otherwise:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 42  Note: multiplied by (select all)
    End If

    Note: FROM clause
    Let from_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "from"
    Let from_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, from_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with from_key

    If from_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "FROM"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

        Note: FROM value can be a string or nested structure
        Let from_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with from_value

        If from_type is equal to 5:  Note: HIR_STRING_LITERAL = 5
            Let table_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with from_value
            proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, table_name
        Otherwise:
            Note: Nested query or expression
            proc generate_hir_node with context, from_value
        End If
    End If

    Note: JOIN clauses
    Let joins_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "joins"
    Let joins_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, joins_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with joins_key

    If joins_list is not equal to 0:
        Let joins_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with joins_list
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than joins_count:
            Let join_node be proc get_list_element from HIR with joins_list, i

            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
            proc generate_join_clause with context, join_node

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: WHERE clause
    Let where_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "where"
    Let where_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, where_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with where_key

    If where_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "WHERE"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, where_value
    End If

    Note: GROUP BY clause
    Let group_by_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "group_by"
    Let group_by_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, group_by_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with group_by_key

    If group_by_list is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "GROUP"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "BY"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_expression_list with context, group_by_list
    End If

    Note: HAVING clause
    Let having_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "having"
    Let having_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, having_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with having_key

    If having_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "HAVING"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, having_value
    End If

    Note: ORDER BY clause
    Let order_by_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "order_by"
    Let order_by_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, order_by_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with order_by_key

    If order_by_list is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "ORDER"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "BY"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_order_by_list with context, order_by_list
    End If

    Note: LIMIT clause
    Let limit_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "limit"
    Let limit_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, limit_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with limit_key

    If limit_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "LIMIT"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, limit_value
    End If

    Note: OFFSET clause
    Let offset_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "offset"
    Let offset_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with select_dict, offset_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with offset_key

    If offset_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "OFFSET"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, offset_value
    End If

    Note: Terminate with semicolon
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 59  Note: ;
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: INSERT Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generate INSERT statements:
INSERT INTO table (col1, col2, ...) VALUES (val1, val2, ...)
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_insert_statement" takes context as Integer, insert_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate INSERT statement from HIR dictionary

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: INSERT INTO keywords
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "INSERT"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "INTO"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with insert_dict, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        Let table_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with table_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, table_name
    End If

    Note: Column list (optional)
    Let columns_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "columns"
    Let columns_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with insert_dict, columns_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with columns_key

    If columns_list is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 40  Note: (
        proc generate_identifier_list with context, columns_list
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
    End If

    Note: VALUES keyword
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "VALUES"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Values list
    Let values_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "values"
    Let values_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with insert_dict, values_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with values_key

    If values_list is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 40  Note: (
        proc generate_expression_list with context, values_list
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
    End If

    Note: Terminate with semicolon
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 59  Note: ;
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: JOIN Clause Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generate JOIN clauses:
[INNER|LEFT|RIGHT|FULL OUTER] JOIN table ON condition
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_join_clause" takes context as Integer, join_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate JOIN clause from HIR dictionary

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Join type (INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL OUTER)
    Let join_type_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "join_type"
    Let join_type_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with join_dict, join_type_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with join_type_key

    If join_type_value is not equal to 0:
        Let join_type_str be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with join_type_value
        Let join_type_len be proc string_length from StringCore with join_type_str

        Note: Emit join type if not INNER (INNER is default)
        Let inner_str be proc create_string from StringCore with "INNER"
        Let is_inner be proc string_equals from StringCore with join_type_str, inner_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with inner_str

        If is_inner is not equal to 1:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, join_type_str
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If
    End If

    Note: JOIN keyword
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "JOIN"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with join_dict, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        Let table_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with table_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, table_name
    End If

    Note: ON condition
    Let on_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "on"
    Let on_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with join_dict, on_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with on_key

    If on_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "ON"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, on_value
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Expression Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generate SQL expressions including binary operations,
function calls, column references, and literals.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_binary_operation" takes context as Integer, binary_op_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate binary operation (e.g., a = b, x > 5, p AND q)

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Get operator
    Let operator_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "operator"
    Let operator_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with binary_op_dict, operator_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with operator_key

    Note: Get left operand
    Let left_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "left"
    Let left_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with binary_op_dict, left_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with left_key

    Note: Get right operand
    Let right_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "right"
    Let right_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with binary_op_dict, right_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with right_key

    Note: Generate: left operator right
    If left_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, left_value
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    If operator_value is not equal to 0:
        Let operator_str be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with operator_value
        proc emit_operator from Emitter with emitter, operator_str
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    If right_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, right_value
    End If
End Process

Process called "generate_function_call" takes context as Integer, function_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate function call: function_name(arg1, arg2, ...)

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Function name
    Let name_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "name"
    Let name_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with function_dict, name_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with name_key

    If name_value is not equal to 0:
        Let function_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with name_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, function_name
    End If

    Note: Arguments
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Let args_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "args"
    Let args_list be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with function_dict, args_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with args_key

    If args_list is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_expression_list with context, args_list
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
End Process

Process called "generate_column_reference" takes context as Integer, column_dict as Integer:
    Note: Generate column reference: [table.]column

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Note: Optional table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with column_dict, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        Let table_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with table_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, table_name
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 46  Note: .
    End If

    Note: Column name
    Let name_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "name"
    Let name_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with column_dict, name_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with name_key

    If name_value is not equal to 0:
        Let column_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with name_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, column_name
    End If

    Note: Optional alias
    Let alias_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "alias"
    Let alias_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with column_dict, alias_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with alias_key

    If alias_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "AS"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

        Let alias_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with alias_value
        proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, alias_name
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: Literal Generation
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Generate SQL literals: integers, floats, strings, booleans, NULL.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_literal" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate literal value

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
    Let node_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with hir_node

    Note: Integer literal
    If node_type is equal to 3:  Note: HIR_INTEGER_LITERAL = 3
        Let int_value be proc get_hir_integer_value from HIR with hir_node
        proc emit_integer from Emitter with emitter, int_value
        Return
    End If

    Note: Float literal
    If node_type is equal to 4:  Note: HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL = 4
        Let float_value be proc get_hir_float_value from HIR with hir_node
        proc emit_float from Emitter with emitter, float_value
        Return
    End If

    Note: String literal
    If node_type is equal to 5:  Note: HIR_STRING_LITERAL = 5
        Let string_value be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with hir_node
        proc emit_string_literal from Emitter with emitter, string_value
        Return
    End If

    Note: Boolean literal
    If node_type is equal to 6:  Note: HIR_BOOLEAN_LITERAL = 6
        Let bool_value be proc get_hir_boolean_value from HIR with hir_node

        If bool_value is equal to 1:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "TRUE"
        Otherwise:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "FALSE"
        End If
        Return
    End If

    Note: NULL literal (represented as 0 in some contexts)
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "NULL"
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: List Generation Helpers
Note: ========================================

@Reasoning:
Helper functions to generate comma-separated lists of various elements.
@End Reasoning

Process called "generate_column_list" takes context as Integer, columns_list as Integer:
    Note: Generate comma-separated column list for SELECT

    Let columns_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with columns_list
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than columns_count:
        Let column_node be proc get_list_element from HIR with columns_list, i

        proc generate_hir_node with context, column_node

        Note: Add comma separator if not last element
        If i is less than columns_count minus 1:
            Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Process called "generate_identifier_list" takes context as Integer, identifiers_list as Integer:
    Note: Generate comma-separated identifier list

    Let identifiers_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with identifiers_list
    Let i be 0
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    While i is less than identifiers_count:
        Let identifier_node be proc get_list_element from HIR with identifiers_list, i

        Note: Identifier can be a string literal
        Let node_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with identifier_node

        If node_type is equal to 5:  Note: HIR_STRING_LITERAL = 5
            Let identifier_name be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with identifier_node
            proc emit_identifier from Emitter with emitter, identifier_name
        Otherwise:
            Note: Handle other identifier representations
            proc generate_hir_node with context, identifier_node
        End If

        Note: Add comma separator if not last element
        If i is less than identifiers_count minus 1:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Process called "generate_expression_list" takes context as Integer, expressions_list as Integer:
    Note: Generate comma-separated expression list

    Let expressions_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with expressions_list
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than expressions_count:
        Let expression_node be proc get_list_element from HIR with expressions_list, i

        proc generate_hir_node with context, expression_node

        Note: Add comma separator if not last element
        If i is less than expressions_count minus 1:
            Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Process called "generate_order_by_list" takes context as Integer, order_by_list as Integer:
    Note: Generate comma-separated ORDER BY list with optional ASC/DESC

    Let order_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with order_by_list
    Let i be 0
    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    While i is less than order_count:
        Let order_item be proc get_list_element from HIR with order_by_list, i

        Note: Check if order_item is a dictionary with "column" and "direction"
        Let item_type be proc get_hir_node_type from HIR with order_item

        If item_type is equal to 7:  Note: HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL = 7
            Note: Extract column
            Let column_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "column"
            Let column_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with order_item, column_key
            proc deallocate from Layout with column_key

            If column_value is not equal to 0:
                proc generate_hir_node with context, column_value
            End If

            Note: Extract direction (optional)
            Let direction_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "direction"
            Let direction_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with order_item, direction_key
            proc deallocate from Layout with direction_key

            If direction_value is not equal to 0:
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32
                Let direction_str be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with direction_value
                proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, direction_str
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Note: Simple expression without direction
            proc generate_hir_node with context, order_item
        End If

        Note: Add comma separator if not last element
        If i is less than order_count minus 1:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: UPDATE Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

Process called "generate_update_statement" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate UPDATE table SET col=val WHERE condition

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "UPDATE"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, table_value
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "SET"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate SET assignments
    Let assignments_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "assignments"
    Let assignments_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, assignments_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with assignments_key

    If assignments_value is not equal to 0:
        Let assignment_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with assignments_value
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than assignment_count:
            Let assignment be proc get_list_element from HIR with assignments_value, i
            proc generate_hir_node with context, assignment

            If i is less than assignment_count minus 1:
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Generate WHERE clause (if present)
    Let where_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "where"
    Let where_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, where_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with where_key

    If where_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "WHERE"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, where_value
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: DELETE Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

Process called "generate_delete_statement" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate DELETE FROM table WHERE condition

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "DELETE"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "FROM"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, table_value
    End If

    Note: Generate WHERE clause (if present)
    Let where_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "where"
    Let where_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, where_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with where_key

    If where_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "WHERE"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
        proc generate_hir_node with context, where_value
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: CREATE TABLE Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

Process called "generate_create_table_statement" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate CREATE TABLE name (columns...)

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "CREATE"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "TABLE"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, table_value
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 40  Note: (

    Note: Generate column definitions
    Let columns_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "columns"
    Let columns_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, columns_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with columns_key

    If columns_value is not equal to 0:
        Let column_count be proc get_list_element_count from HIR with columns_value
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than column_count:
            Let column_def be proc get_list_element from HIR with columns_value, i
            proc generate_hir_node with context, column_def

            If i is less than column_count minus 1:
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 44  Note: ,
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: ALTER TABLE Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

Process called "generate_alter_table_statement" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate ALTER TABLE name action

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "ALTER"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space
    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "TABLE"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate table name
    Let table_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
    Let table_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, table_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with table_key

    If table_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, table_value
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate ALTER action
    Let action_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "action"
    Let action_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, action_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with action_key

    If action_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, action_value
    End If
End Process

Note: ========================================
Note: DROP Statement Generation
Note: ========================================

Process called "generate_drop_statement" takes context as Integer, hir_node as Integer:
    Note: Generate DROP TABLE/INDEX name

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "DROP"
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate object type
    Let obj_type_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "object_type"
    Let obj_type_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, obj_type_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with obj_type_key

    If obj_type_value is not equal to 0:
        Let obj_type_str be proc get_hir_string_value from HIR with obj_type_value

        Let table_str be proc create_string from StringCore with "table"
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with obj_type_str, table_str is equal to 1:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "TABLE"
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with table_str

        Let index_str be proc create_string from StringCore with "index"
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with obj_type_str, index_str is equal to 1:
            proc emit_keyword from Emitter with emitter, "INDEX"
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with index_str
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: space

    Note: Generate object name
    Let name_key be proc create_string from StringCore with "name"
    Let name_value be proc get_dictionary_value from HIR with hir_node, name_key
    proc deallocate from Layout with name_key

    If name_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_hir_node with context, name_value
    End If
End Process

Note: End of HIR to SQL Generator
